==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Quass
<hw>Quass</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Russ.
<ets>kvas'</ets>.]</ety> <def>A thin, sour beer, made by pouring warm
water on rye or barley meal and letting it ferment, -- much used by the
Russians. Called also <altname>kvass</altname>.</def> <altsp>[written
also <asp>kvass</asp> and <asp>quas</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quassation</ent>⟦br⟧
